##I'm doing renovations at Thor Mountain: Putting up a building in three days

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Deng Yafei, intern, Chen Zijia, _ thepaper.cn _

"I always thought that if I saw the news about Thor Mountain Hospital on TV in the future, I would be very proud and proud. I will tell people that I decorated this building, that this is where my colleagues and I are competing for time, and that in the end we did it without delaying the patients who needed this hospital."

On February 8th, Thor Mountain Hospital was delivered on time. Deng Yi, the technical manager of the decoration, is one of the numerous builders of the Raytheon Mountain Hospital.

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, construction of the Vulcan Mountain Hospital had just begun, and the new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters in Wuhan held an emergency dispatch meeting and decided to build another one within half a month.

Over the course of six days, the total planning of the Gross leasable area was increased three times, from 50,000 square meters to 79,900 square meters, and the number of beds increased from 1,300 to 1,600. The overall size of the hospital exceeded two Vulcan Mountain hospitals, but the construction period was comparable to that of Vulcan Mountain, behind this is the hard work of thousands of ordinary people.

On February 3, Deng Yi and his colleagues, who work for the century-old brand of Hubei Fujikura Building Materials Technology Co. , Ltd. , resolutely accepted the "hero post" to support the construction of Wuhan Thunder Mountain Hospital. "after the completion of each building, my colleagues and I have to complete the interior decoration in three to five days. My team and I have decorated three buildings, and one building in three days at the earliest, " Deng told The Paper www.thepaper.cn  .

Deng Yi admitted that he had done decoration also rush time, have been working all night, but never so eager to finish. He added that he was also afraid of being infected when he first arrived in Wuhan. "until one time, when I saw builders lining up for hours, I was like, 'this is such a big construction team! Since no one is afraid, I'm not afraid either. ' "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Deng Yi and his decoration team. Photos are provided for the interviewees

Dictation by Deng Yi

An hour of food and sleep is a luxury

Every morning, we start work at 7 am, but get up at 6 am to get ready because the bunkhouse is nearly a 40 minute drive from the construction site at Thor Mountain.

Accommodation in the shed is temporary requisition, in fact, is the Mobile Board Room, so the environment is relatively difficult.

However, we were prepared and didn't really have much time to sleep in the bunkhouse. We all know what it means to have to deliver the hospital on time, time is of the essence, all the workers are working overtime, we go back to the shed to sleep every day at about two or three in the morning, sometimes even need to work all night.

We are not iron man, but the problem in front of us is really not small, large construction and time constraints.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Construction workers work at night.

I am mainly responsible for the decoration, involving the more types of work, including plumbing, carpentry, bricklayer and so on. Our work is wiring, piping, so that the Thor Mountain Hospital can be connected to water and electricity. That's a lot of work. Every ward in the hospital has its own bathroom with its own hot and cold water system, lighting, ventilation, and air purification.

The requirement given to us is to decorate one building in 3 to 5 days, now we have finished the interior decoration of 3 buildings on time, the fastest time is 3 days to complete a building.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The workers wired the room.

I will also arrange the connection between materials and skilled workers, and the distribution of workers'work. I am now responsible for the distribution of 15 to 20 workers, every morning morning meeting to assign everyone's work, evening party to do the day's work summary, and put together to do the work the next day.

Because of the wide area involved in the deployment and connection of building materials, sometimes the delivery of materials will be delayed, sometimes there will be problems in the process, such as I did this step, but the last step is not completed. This kind of time needs to wait and link up, fortunately, everyone is doing their job, so this kind of situation or less.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The workmen are treating the boards in the room.

Another thing that is particularly different from decoration in normal times is that because the construction period is so short, workers of each type of work are working at the same time. Sometimes everyone is crowded together, and they have to be careful when they turn around, i don't want to crash everyone else's work schedule.

We've worked all night and all night, but we've never been so eager to get it done.

In order to ensure physical strength, lunch for an hour, became the time for people to catch up on sleep. Sometimes I feel sorry for my colleagues who fall asleep all over the place and jump right in when it's time. Think of this hour as a luxury.

Friends from all over the world may never see each other again

These few days at Mount Thor, I actually enjoyed the short time before I ate and went to bed. Not just because it's a break, but because it's a chance to talk to the workers.

We are a group of builders from all over the world, we get together because of the Thor Mountain hospital, together construction, eat together, together to talk about their home interesting things. Perhaps we a few people in the daytime still can because of the problem of construction join"urgent eye", but sit down to chat a few words, what all passed.

I call it "revolutionary friendship. " We are not as distinguished as soldiers, but I think we are also comrades-in-arms.

At the end of each day's work on the construction site, we chat on wechat groups. In addition to exchanging project progress and work experience, we mostly joke and tell jokes. After all, these are also the forces that keep us going.

To tell you the truth, I haven't known the workers for long, and it's very difficult to establish a deep friendship in the last few days. But the time I spent with them, I'll never forget.

Everyone says we should celebrate when it's done, but at this particular time, parties are definitely not allowed. This is a small regret, because the next time to see these "comrades" , do not know when, perhaps, never have the opportunity to meet it.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo of Deng Yi and the decoration team.

The best part of every day is telling your child, I'm safe

In fact, before coming to Wuhan, I also thought that I might be infected, and I was also afraid. But when I saw on TV that people started working on the first and second day of the first lunar month, I was inspired.

I saw so many people working on this outbreak, and to think that no one was afraid, so what was I afraid of?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers work at Thor Mountain Hospital.

I've been hearing the word "retrograde" a lot lately, and I'm not sure how great "retrograde" is, but I think every decision we make has to be worthy of our family.

My family was against it at first. My parents said to me: "Wuhan side of the epidemic is quite serious, do not go over, they said it is too late to escape Wuhan, how do you still run to Wuhan! "

I told them, "a lot of people are doing their part for the epidemic, and I want to do something about it. " Then they understood and supported me, and before I left, my wife urged me to take care of myself and to take care of myself.

My 9-year-old is so reluctant to let me go that he texts me every day, "How are you, Dad? Are you okay? When are you coming home? " And then, i am the happiest and most dependable person in my life, telling my children and family, "I am safe. ".

Working in such a special place, I do not know why, I became very homesick, especially miss my parents, wife and children, but I did not tell them too much, for fear that they would worry.

I always thought that if I saw the news about Thor Mountain Hospital on TV in the future, I would be very proud, very proud. I would tell people that that was where my colleagues and I were competing for time, and we did it in the end, without delaying the patients who needed this hospital.

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
